The time of his beheading we find out by those words of the evangelist John b, “ but now the Passover was nigh,” by reasoning after this manner: It may be concluded, without all controversy, that the discipleS, as soon as they heard of the death of their master, and buried him, betook them- selves to Christ, relating his slaughter, and giving him cau- tion by that example to take care of his own safety.
